<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="119" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,335,880,906]" box="[189,335,880,906]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,880,906]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,880,906]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,887,927,989]" box="[234,378,927,954]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,927,953]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Male</emphasis>
(n=1)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,887,927,989]" box="[189,887,962,989]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
Length: 
<quantity box="[288,359,963,989]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[524,654,962,988]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[524,654,962,988]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">D. phoenix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[662,752,963,989]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[187,1399,1028,1407]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
Frons about 0.28 × head width at level of ocellar triangle; 10 well-developed frontal setae reaching level of apex of pedicel; first flagellomere approximately 4 × as long as pedicel; acrostichals 3 (weakly differentiated) +1; intra-alars 2+ 2, postpronotals 2; meral setae 7–8; vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1114,1123,1117,1131]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">1</subScript>
setulose; row of about 10 marginal setae on T5; marginal setae of ST2–4 slightly differentiated from discal setae; surstylus almost triangular (
<figureCitation box="[405,500,1169,1196]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); pregonite 1.5× as long as postgonite, base narrow, apex broad and anterior margin dilated at middle (
<figureCitation box="[487,577,1204,1231]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); postgonite broad, with long seta inserted at middle of anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[196,289,1239,1266]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); two longitudinal keels along posterior margin of basiphallus, and paraphallus with few short spines along ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[523,613,1274,1301]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); vesica rectangular, with apical projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1384,1274,1301]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
); juxta smooth and recessed within paraphallus (
<figureCitation box="[755,887,1309,1336]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C–D</figureCitation>
); median stylus robust, longer than lateral stylus and with base bent dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[609,703,1345,1372]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
); lateral stylus with enlarged base slightly twisted towards ventral margin of paraphallus and with apical spines (
<figureCitation box="[819,949,1380,1407]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
