<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,1658,1684]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[188,1399,1704,1907]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,520,1704,1730]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patiuorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,520,1704,1730]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Dexosarcophaga patiuorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[527,617,1705,1731]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mello-Patiu, 2000" authorityName="Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2000" box="[969,1276,1704,1731]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guyi">
<emphasis box="[969,1055,1705,1730]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">D. guyi</emphasis>
Mello-Patiu, 2000
</taxonomicName>
by having basiphallus with two longitudinal keels and paraphallus with short spines (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1168,1739,1766]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
; Mello-Patiu 2000: figs 4, 7). These two species can be differentiated by the following features: vesica rectangular, with an apical projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[572,663,1810,1837]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), and paraphallus with short spines on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1300,1390,1810,1837]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[218,1317,310,1795]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[189,1398,302,1816]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. Dexosarcophaga patiuorum sp. nov., ♂, holotype (MNRJ [lost]). A. Syntergosternite 7+8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. B. Cerci, posterior view. C. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. D. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars=0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823742" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823742/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[221,556,1845,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patiuorum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[221,556,1845,1871]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Dexosarcophaga patiuorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[566,662,1846,1872]" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, versus vesica triangular in lateral view and paraphallus with short spines on dorsal margin (Mello-Patiu 2000: figs 4, 7) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2000" box="[914,1173,1880,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guyi">
<emphasis box="[914,1173,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="119">Dexosarcophaga guyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
